<tt>Thu Nov 28 21:11:23 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I spent 15 years trying to pretend like I'd never been there,  I would tell you I was therer but I couldn;t tell you or myself what I felt there except for the really big moments like a lot of rage or fear,  Then I found myself being jolted back to waking just as I was dropping off to sleep, my heart pumping, sweating, certain someone was in the room with a gun about to kill me or that I had been sentence die when I awoke, only to awak and find all this physical evidence of threat without any reality to substantiate it.  No one in the room, no sentece impending, just a blank mind and a terrified body.  1986 and I found my way to several 12 step programs and the VA Vet centers.  I worked on addiction issues(my own and those of family members) and looked into what Viet Nam had left in its aftermath in my life.  Sat with a lot of sick Vets in a lot of meetings.  Learned to meditate,  Read &quot;Back from the Brink&quot; that told me to get with my wife and tell her what hapened to me.  Wrong.  The author had failed to realize most trauma survivors had enough self-hate to virtually guarantee they would be paired with someone who hated them as mus\ch as they hated themselves and who was a trauma survivor herself.  It got ugly or I should say the ugliness came to the surface.  17 therapists in 5 years,  Gulf War,  /saw a couple of Vet buddies go down and not come back up.  Bunkered up with their television,  Had to be taken away.  PBS interviewed me about how it was to be in war the night it was over.  Drove home in a rage listening to President JohnsonNixonBush talk about those brave kids defending us.  Yeah fuck head isn't it supposed to be the other way around, shouldn't we be defending them, defending their right to grow up, their right to find out about life before they are thrown into the killing zone?  Bush says we're finally over Viet Nam now that we've ba\ombed the shit out of Iraq for a few weeks.  How does he get that?  How does more war get us over the last one?  How does sending another generation into harm's way get us over the hundreds of thousands of kids we sent into battle in a country we didn't begin to understand or really even care about?  How does it get us over the lies we told ourselves and each other?  How does it get us over the 2.5 million Vietnamese peaople killed?  How does it get us over the defense industry that made a profit on the war?  How does it get us over the 58000 families who lost sons and fathers and brothers and grandsons?  Come on president fuckhead talk about that and all the other damage that war visited upon this nation and the other nations of the world.<br><br>
1993 had it with the VA had it with therapy, had it with my marriage to a woman who really didn't like me nor I her.  Started a trauma survivors group for trauma survivors of all types: war, violence, rape, incest, abusive family whatever.  It ran for three years and was visited by over 50 people most of whom were never in the republic of Viet Nam.  Used the book &quot;Conscious Loving&quot; as a guide and began to heal.  Peak moment was a meeting in which I shared with the froup every dirty secret I was carrying and none of them were about Viet Nam.  All of them were about the incest and sexual dysfundtion in my family and in myself.  I had already found that the roots of what happened to me in VietNam were in my family and that when I got to what happened there, what happened innn VN cleared.  <br><br>
1996  NEw house, New marriage, New baby.  New job,  New feeling in my head.  I am dealing with the pain of success instead of the agony of defeat.  Am finding success harder.  New trauma group in the works.  It will be based in Teamwork theory and new bool called &quot;Trauma and Recovery&quot;  This is a must read for anyone on the path of healing from whatever happened to you.  Still working with the book &quot;COnscious Loving&quot; another must read.  It says that we store our trauma in our subconscious where it saves our lives but begins to use up pur creative energy.  Clearing traum out of the subconscious allows it to be used to manifest success and wholeness in our lives.  Am finding this to be true although it is deeplly challenging nonetheless.  <br><br>
Future  I want to continue to heal and to continue to facilitate the healing of others.  New trauma group is one way.  Believe that there is a need for a political party with the healing of trauma as its main platform.  Imagine political commercials with trauma suvivors telling their stories instead of the boring and insulting trash we get now.  Political conventions that are for trauma survivors to come and tell their stories and to get together to heal and grieve.  Grieve for the Viet Nam war, WWII, the Korean War, WWI, the Indian Wars, the abused children of America, the incested gamilies of America, The batterd wives of America, The raped women of America, The young men and women abused in training in the service of their country....<br>
Sounds like a different sort of political party to me.  What about it?
